                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Winship Mission/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Special Commissioner for Liberia (<persName type="to"
                        >Winship</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 20, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Your telegram No. 38, April 19, 6 p.m. Your message has been communicated to
                    Firestone Junior who states that instructions will be sent to Lyle tonight
                    giving him requisite latitude to continue negotiations. Firestone wishes you to
                    know that previous instruction to Lyle was the result of a misunderstanding as
                    he did not then know you had obtained from Barclay the statement that Liberian
                    counter proposals were point of departure for further discussions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
